en_276002_0	The much-needed two Samsung HS40 Ultrasound Scanner Units, purchased from the day’s pay of Army personnel were formally handed over to Maharagama ‘Apeksha’ Cancer Hospital this morning (17) by the think-tank of the meritorious project, Lieutenant General Mahesh Senanayake, Commander of the Army.
en_276002_1	On arrival, the day’s Chief Guest Lieutenant General Mahesh Senanayake, Commander of the Army was warmly welcomed by Dr Wasantha Dissanayake, Director, Maharagama ‘Apeksha’ Hospital and members of the Association to Fight Against Cancer.
en_276002_2	Dr Wasantha Dissanayake, Director, ‘Apeksha’ Hospital during the brief handover ceremony explained how the entire project got to a start when he one day met his former schoolmate at Ananda College, Lieutenant General Mahesh Senanayake who inquired from him whether the Army could do anything to alleviate the suffering of Cancer patients, particularly small children.
en_276002_3	“The Army commanded by my old pal afterwards responded back and promised to buy those scanners for the benefit of all cancer patients”, Dr Dissanayake quipped.
en_276002_4	Lieutenant General Senanayake also made a brief speech to the occasion.
en_276002_5	During the ceremony to award ‘Parama Weera Vibhushanaya’ (PWV) medal to War Heroes on War Heroes’ Day (22 May), Lieutenant General Mahesh Senanayake officially presented Rs 8.2 million worth cheque to HE the President Maithripala Sirisena who was instrumental in getting those new scanners.
en_276002_6	After all Army personnel were educated on the need to purchase those vital units each member of the Army volunteered to donate a day’s pay for this worthy cause.
en_276002_7	As a result, their generosity enabled Cancer Hospital authorities to buy two scanner units, instead of one.
en_276002_8	Ultrasound scans, or sonography, are safe because they use sound waves or echoes to make an image, instead of radiation.
en_276002_9	Ultrasound scans are used to evaluate fetal development and they can detect problems in the liver, heart, kidney, or abdomen.
en_276002_10	They may also assist in performing certain types of biopsies.
